com.poesys.db.dao.delete

Class DeleteByKey<T extends IDbDto>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dao.delete.DeleteByKey<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of IDbDto to delete
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDelete<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DeleteCacheByKey, DeleteMemcachedByKey

    public class DeleteByKey<T extends IDbDto>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDelete<T>
    An implementation of the IDelete interface that updates an object, identifying the object in the database using the primary key of the data transfer object (DTO). Note that the SQL statement can be null for deletes that are done through the database rather than through the application.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller
    See Also:
    IDeleteSql

        public void delete(java.sql.Connection connection,
                   T dto)
            throws java.sql.SQLException,
                   BatchException
        Description copied from interface: IDelete
        Delete the contents of a DTO object in the database. The DTO must contain values for the primary key. The DTO must have any setters required to preprocess nested objects that must be handled before deleting the object.
        Specified by:
        delete in interface IDelete<T extends IDbDto>
        Parameters:
        connection - the database connection with which to delete the data
        dto - the IDto data transfer object containing the primary key
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - when there is a SQL error with the delete
        BatchException - when there is a problem deleting or updating a nested collection of linked objects
